- used for restriction
- final keyword can be used in

1. Variable
	eg. final int a = 10
	- can not change/update value
	- final variable that have no value(blank final variable or uninitialized final variable)
	- blank final variable can be initialized in constructor only
	- blank final static variable can be initialized in static block only

2. Method -
	eg. final void show(){
	}
	- we cannot override final method

3. class
	eg. final class Test{
	}
	- we cannot extend final class

Can we declare a constructor as final?
No,
